parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Safety Belt Buckle Release Button Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front safety belt buckle release button can cause the buckle to operate improperly, leading to the seat belt not catching or holding properly, which can result in injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The release button breaks
pieces fall into the buckle assembly
the buckle does not latch or hold properly
the seat belt becomes unlatched
the buckle is hard to lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt can cause the belt to not stay fastened, which can result in injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belt will not stay fastened
the belt unlooses itself
the locking mechanism pops out and releases the belt
the belt fails to work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repairs can lead to continued use of faulty seat belts, which can result in injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealer does not have parts to perform recall repairs
recall notice received but dealer still does not have parts
excessive time taken for recall notifications to go out.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Automatic Transmission and Torque Converter Failure
